    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-06-20T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-06-20T18:00:00-05:00" n="348"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d348">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">795.00/6–951: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in India</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-06-20T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 20, 1951—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2225. Urtel 3567 Jun 9. Secy’s statement Jun 2 on settlement in Korea is
                    correctly quoted <hi rend="italic">N.Y. Times</hi> Jun 3 page 65 columns 4, 5,
                    and 6, and has also been transmitted to you by airgram.</p>
                <p>Decision whether Panikkar approach <gloss target="#t_Chicom1">Chicom</gloss>s on
                    basis Secy’s testimony to determine whether Secy’s statements provide basis for
                    discussion entirely one for independent determination by <gloss target="#t_GOI1"
                        >GOI</gloss>. However if this is done suggest <gloss target="#t_GOI1"
                        >GOI</gloss> provide Panikkar full text, as second para <gloss
                        target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss> appears indicate Panikkar does not have
                    full understanding Secy’s statements. In particular note shld be made of
                    necessity for reliable assurances against renewal aggression, and that issues
                    relating to Formosa and <gloss target="#t_Chicom1">Chicom</gloss> admission UN
                    not a part of Korean question.</p>
                <p>Secy’s statements entirely consistent with many other expressions <pb facs="0555"
                        n="539" xml:id="pg_539"/> US policy set forth in public statements by Pres,
                    and by other US officials in UN and elsewhere. No additional formal statements
                    US views believed required at this time.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
